                   "message":  "fix(dispatch): guard hardening -- path anchoring + assess stdin delivery + diagnosability\n\nFixes the two safety-layer bugs surfaced by the first live guarded tick\n(TICK114B/TICK114C), before any further autonomous runs.\n\n1. Path anchoring (TICK114B startup death). PowerShell cmdlets resolve relative\n   paths against $PWD while [System.IO.File] APIs resolve against the process\n   .NET current directory; with a relative -WatchRoot and mismatched anchors the\n   guard created its watch dir in one place and aimed its first log write at\n   another, dying before START. Fix: absolutize -WatchRoot against $PWD (join\n   BEFORE GetFullPath so normalization never consults the .NET cwd) and pin\n   [System.Environment]::CurrentDirectory to $PWD so residual relative use\n   (e.g. -DriverCommand via Start-Process) resolves consistently.\n\n2. Assess delivery (TICK114C \"no activity\" verdicts). Passing the multi-line\n   rubric as one argv (\u0026 claude -p $rubric) mangled it under PS 5.1: the JSON\n   format spec\u0027s embedded quotes shatter the argument during native argv\n   quoting + npm-shim re-splat, and the \"Recent activity\" tail never reached\n   the model. Reproduced through the guard\u0027s exact code path (blatant rm -rf\n   anomaly -\u003e verdict=ok \"no recent activity was provided\"). Fix: deliver the\n   prompt via STDIN through a new mockable seam (Invoke-MonitorModel); same\n   anomaly now -\u003e verdict=abort citing the destructive action and skipped gate.\n\n3. Diagnosability (operator requirement). Every assessment persists its exact\n   prompt to the watch dir (assess-NNN.prompt.txt) and logs an ASSESSCTX line\n   with promptChars/activityChars, so any future \"no activity\" claim is\n   immediately attributable to construction vs delivery.\n\nTests: new Pester coverage recreates TICK114B (child process with $PWD vs .NET\ncwd mismatch + relative -WatchRoot must complete with the log under $PWD) and\ncovers the assess seam CI-safe via Mock (canary activity must be inside the\nprompt handed to the model + persisted; abort propagates; empty response fails\nclosed). Suite 64/64; PSScriptAnalyzer (repo settings) 0 findings; dry-run\n0/2/2; live final-drain + multi-tick tests unchanged and green; real-claude\nsmoke through the patched path validated locally.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
